verses.verse: (For the choir director; with stringed instruments. A Psalm. A Song.) <S%H430>God<s%> be <S%H2603>gracious<s%> to us and <S%H1288>bless<s%> us, [And] cause His <S%H6440>face<s%> to <S%H215>shine<s%> upon us â€“ <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
That Thy <S%H1870>way<s%> may be <S%H3045>known<s%> on the <S%H776>earth,<s%> Thy <S%H3444>salvation<s%> among <S%H3605>all<s%> <S%H1471>nations.<s%>
Let the <S%H5971>peoples<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> Thee, O <S%H430>God;<s%> Let <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H5971>peoples<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> Thee.

Let the <S%H3816>nations<s%> be <S%H8055>glad<s%> and <S%H7442>sing<s%> for <S%H7442>joy;<s%> For Thou wilt <S%H8199>judge<s%> the <S%H5971>peoples<s%> with <S%H4334>uprightness,<s%> And <S%H5148>guide<s%> the <S%H3816>nations<s%> on the <S%H776>earth.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
Let the <S%H5971>peoples<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> Thee, O <S%H430>God;<s%> Let <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H5971>peoples<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> Thee.
<S%H430>God<s%> <S%H1288>blesses<s%> us, That <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H657>ends<s%> of the <S%H776>earth<s%> may <S%H3372>fear<s%> Him.
